Feature: Intelligence Architecture for Regenerative Communities

  As a regenerative community
  I want a knowledge system that connects self-referring loops
  So that retrieval, action, governance, and feedback operate as one coherent system

  Background:
    Given 17 wiki sources and 11 concepts define the community knowledge base
    And Ben Goertzel's algorithmic chemistry provides the cognitive substrate
    And Karpathy's LLM wiki pattern provides compiled retrieval without manual indexing
    And MCP standardizes how agents connect to tools

  Scenario: Community queries knowledge via natural language
    Given a member asks "nitrogen-fixing trees near waterlogged soil"
    When the system performs sparse BM25 search and dense HNSW search
    And combines results using Reciprocal Rank Fusion
    Then results show 20-49% improvement over single-method retrieval
    And individual token matches are honored even when full-sequence similarity is lower

  Scenario: Self-catalyzing programs produce emergent cognition
    Given algorithmic chemistry defines programs that rewrite programs
    When catalytic code drives self-organizing cognitive systems
    Then emergent cognition arises through self-reinforcing rewrite loops
    And no manual indexing is required to maintain the knowledge structure

  Scenario: Agents use other agents as tools
    Given a high-level goal is set by a community member
    When the system decomposes the goal into sub-tasks
    And assigns specialized agents to each sub-task
    Then autonomous execution proceeds with minimal human intervention
    And the full loop from goal to result completes without manual oversight

  Scenario: Agent skills package institutional knowledge
    Given an AI coding assistant needs community-specific knowledge
    When it reads a SKILL.md file encoding institutional practices
    Then the agent executes with community-aligned behavior
    And the knowledge remains reusable across multiple agent invocations

  Scenario: Governance decisions affect real-world outcomes
    Given a collective of agents must decide on resource allocation
    When the governance protocol evaluates evidence-based performance
    Then influence flows to what's working
    And losing approaches fade while successful ones replicate
    And no single entity can dominate the decision process

  Scenario: Knowledge retrieval at civilizational scale
    Given knowledge infrastructure has reached Phase 3 criticality
    When the community cannot function without digital coordination systems
    Then the system provides reliable retrieval under all conditions
    And offline operation continues without cloud dependency
    And P2P sync maintains consistency across mesh networks

  Scenario: Meta-layer connects all four architectural threads
    Given algorithmic chemistry produces emergent cognition
    And knowledge graphs provide compiled retrieval over structured corpora
    And agent skills package institutional knowledge for autonomous execution
    And governance protocols handle collective decision-making with real-world consequences
    When the meta-layer connects all four threads
    Then a civilizational operating system emerges for communities
    And knowledge retrieval, autonomous action, governance, and regenerative feedback operate as one system
